J.P. Morgan Asset Management Hires John Anderson From Gartmore

-- B y   A n c h a l e e   W o r r a c h a t e
-- 
2011-04-07T16:25:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/j-p-morgan-asset-management-hires-john-anderson-from-gartmore.html
J.P. Morgan Asset Management hired
 John Anderson  from Gartmore Investment Management Ltd. to be a
portfolio manager in its fixed-income team.  Anderson will report to Lisa Coleman, head of credit, and
will manage the Sterling Corporate Bond Fund, which has 52.8
million pounds ($86 million) in assets, the unit of JPMorgan
Chase & Co. said in a statement today.  Anderson previously worked at Rensburg Fund Management.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Anchalee Worrachate in London at 
 aworrachate@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Daniel Tilles at 
 dtilles@bloomberg.net  